Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses Natural Language Processing techniques to automatically extract sound changes and model sound change using a Bayesian hierarchical mixed-membership model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a probabilistic approach and Bayesian modeling to assess the validity of the Inner-Outer hypothesis. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning and probabilistic modeling to analyze linguistic data. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on sound changes in Indo-Aryan languages and how they relate to the Inner-Outer hypothesis. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper may also be relevant to the study of language and culture in society.
